main event: A ground-radar tracked an unidentified object for approximately 2 minutes near Ridgecrest, California on January 29, 1952.
interesting points: The object appeared as a bright echo on the radar but suddenly faded and disappeared.
There were no visual sightings of the object.
The report concludes the sighting as an 'Unknown' and possible 'Electronic Interference'.
The document does not contain any photographs.
The report is a Project Blue Book record card from the United States Air Force.
